bio.experienceSummary:
Hey there! My names Victoria. I am a recent graduate from SCAD Atlanta and love working with kids. Creativity is my passion, whether it be teaching crafting/building projects, coming up with silly songs, or engaging with your child in imaginary play!

I have cared for children ages 0-15 and have 1. 5 years of full time nannying experience with a family of 2 children (ages 2 and 7). I have 6 years experience of general babysitting. 

I currently am working a full time job but would love to help out on weekends, for monthly date nights, or evenings here and there! 

I look forward to hearing from you and your family!!

I am a current college student with a little over 6 years of babysitting experience and I am looking for a source of income through something I love. I am a big sister of four kids(ages 9-11) and an occasional family babysitter. I can provide you with an active, energetic, and interactive babysitter. I can help with housekeeping and educational needs. If you need any help with planning or organizing I can also help with that. With my experience, I will be able to provide you with both a trustworthy babysitter and a safe environment for your little ones.

description.originalText: Jaberia was our nanny from the time our daughter was 12 weeks old until almost 6 months old. She was an excellent caregiver with great patience. Jaberia helped our daughter to develop motor skills that set her on a great path. Our baby loves Jaberia and smiled so big when she arrived every morning. I would definitely recommend hiring Jaberia as your nanny and/or babysitter. Sheâ€™s a kind soul and very trustworthy. Always arrived on time and came early if needed.

bio.experienceSummary:
I have worked in early childhood care and education for over 10 years.
I am comfortable with pets.
I have 2 children 4 and 6 years old, I'm very comfortable with children with special needs as my son has autism and both of my children have adhd.
I am very energetic and love doing things like crafts and science experiments with the kids.
I also enjoy singing and music and dancing.


I like working with kids because I love watching them grow and learn and develop their little personalities.
I love assisting children with creative problem solving and emotional regulation.

I started working with kids when I was 14 my mother had triplet girls, I fell in love with being a big sister and taking care of little ones.

In my spare time, I like to take my children on adventures or go hiking with my husband and dog Tucker.

description.originalText: Brittany is wonderful with children. She worked for me for over a year- responsible, reliable. The kids were always happy and very well taken care of. I definitely recommend her!

bio.experienceSummary: As an energetic babysitter with a rich background spanning 7 years. I excel in crafting engaging activities that cater to both their educational and physical needs, all while maintaining a vigilant focus on health and safety. I consistently go above and beyond to establish a fun, safe, and stimulating environment for their children. I am dedicated to ensuring a positive and nurturing experience for every child under my care. Please reach out if you have any questions or want to see my references ! I'm looking for a job that is okay with making me feel that I'm apart of the family. Willing to work hand in hand to provide the best care for the children. I thrive on the opportunity to develop personal connections with both the family and the children, I believe in creating a nurturing environment where every child feels valued and supported, and I am excited to contribute to that vision in a collaborative and creative way.

My name is Nancy and I am a 31-year-old looking to nanny full-time. I have over 11 years of experience caring for children ages 0- 14 as a private nanny and have several excellent references. My goal is to make sure the children in my care are stimulated and have fun while providing an opportunity to learn and experience new things in a safe and nurturing environment. I love writing, reading, outdoors, yoga, theater, arts and crafts, learning and having a good time!

I'm not only a great sitter, I'm an awesome role model for your child! I value safety, education and having a good time. I've earned a BA in Psychology from CAU and a M. Ed in Educational Studies from Johns Hopkins University. I've been in the childcare business for 8+ years now, but have always been passionate about caring for kids. I spent 2 years as a teacher in kindergarten and first grade at a charter school in Washington, DC. I have worked with infants as young as 3 months, and children as old as 11 years. I have lots of experience with toddlers ages 1-5. I have tons of experience driving kids to and from school, after-school activities, outings and appointments. I love to help with homework and school projects. Children and education are my passions and helping each child reach their full potential in life is my purpose.

description.originalText: Amazing, Gifted. A natural with children. Strong recommend!

bio.experienceSummary: Over 10 years of child care experience with in and out door activities as well as cooking nutritional meals and educational activities , arts and crafts, pets are not a problem as well. I have an SUV so car size is not a problem. I have the most calm and patience for little kids and babies. I work well with all ages.

description.originalText: Kenyatta worked for me and my family for she was awesome with our 2 and 5 year old. She made sure she helped with homework and tutoring.She prepared nutritional meals, ensured children had daily naps. always  read books to the children during the day and at bedtime. Also made sure children had outdoor activities.

bio.experienceSummary: Hey everyone! My name is Elisabeth but I go by my middle name, Abigail and I am currently a (sports) journalism major student. I have experience with pets of all sizes and ages. I am especially knowledgeable with senior dogs. I have 3 years of Early Childhood Education/Development education, over 5 years experience with all ages, and CPR training. I love to be outside at the park, do crafts, help with homework, play sports, and watch a good movie every now and then! Please do not hesitate to reach out! (:

Hi there, 
I am Victoria and I have been working with children professionally since 2015. Before that I spent my time volunteering at my church and a shelter for disabled women with children. I got into childcare in college working for the YMCA summer camp just to make some extra money and immediately fell in love. There was something about working with children with all their different needs, personalities and love that made me truly happy. Since then I've held different positions with the YMCA and The Boys and Girls Club, as well as two daycare centers as a teacher. I have worked with every age group from infants teens, all having their own challenges and joys. I am currently a teacher with Memphis Shelby County schools where I have taught 2nd grade for two years. I love education and finding ways to make it fun. Dancing, creating STEAM based projects, and learning new things with children is right up my alley. I look forward to helping a new family soon.

My name is Lillian. I graduated from Temple in 2021 with a Bachelors in Early Childhood education. I have many years of experience with children in classrooms and private homes. During the summer of 2019, l worked as a pre-K teacher and I've been working in childcare ever since. Throughout college, I had numerous babysitting jobs and completed coursework to become a teacher. After I graduated I began nannying fulltime.
I enjoy working with children and being a positive role model in their lives. I have experience with ages 4mo to 12yrs. I'm active, patient, reliable, easygoing, an excellent communicator, and can pick up on new routines quickly. Safety is my top priority. In past jobs I have driven kids to/from school and extracurriculars, meal prepped, helped with laundry, helped with homework, and put kids to bed at night. I'm also available to do occasional overnight sitting if that's ever a need. I am a career nanny with a passion for what I do.

description.displayText: Lillian has been our sitter for over 5 years. Our daughter is now 8 and Lillian is her favorite sitter. We can't say enough about her. She truly loves children and has a knack for keeping them engaged. She's professional, dependable and patient.
